'''Benjamin O. Jimerson-Phillips''' is an African American movie producer, director, songwriter, and screenwriter.<ref name="Houston Style Magazine">{{cite journal |title=Benjamin O. Jimerson|publisher= Minority Print Media, L.L.C. |volume=18 |page= 9|accessdate=16 June 2013|format=news journal}}</ref> Also known as Benjamin O. Jimerson, with Adept Films Inc., as well as owner Jimerson & Associates founded in 1995.<ref name="Jimerson & Associates ">{{cite web|title=About Us |url= http://www.jimersonandassociates.com/About.html|publisher= Jimerson & Associates |accessdate=5 May 2013|pages=1|year=2013}}</ref> Aside from his film related work he also is an established screen writer, and has also authored three published books. Notable for being a pro-life activist, and humanitarian.<ref name=""A Day In The Life"... ">{{cite book|title= "A Day In The Life"... |publisher=Create Space |isbn=1466347724 |accessdate=16 June 2013|type=Hardcover}}</ref>

==Biography==
Benjamin O. Jimerson-Philips, also known as "Ben Jimerson" was born to  parents Jessie Jimerson-Phillips, and J.O. Patterson Sr.,<ref name="Local men talk about their relationship with MLK Jr.">{{cite web|title= Local men talk about their relationship with MLK Jr.|url= http://www.kob.com/article/stories/S3290202.shtml?cat=500#.Ut37xo3Tncc|publisher= Eyewitness News 4 |accessdate=20 January 2014|pages=1|year=2014}}</ref><ref name=" Prodigal Son, Child of The King">{{cite book|title= Prodigal Son, Child of The King |publisher=Create Space |isbn=1475109881  |accessdate=5 May 2013|type=Hardcover}}</ref> being the eldest of their two children.<ref name=" J. O. Patterson Ministry Official Homepage ">{{cite web|title=Home Page |url=http://www.jopattersonministry.com/Home.html|publisher= J. O. Patterson Ministry |accessdate=5 May 2013|pages=1|year=2013}}</ref> He attended the Sabarbaro Elementary School (now know as Author Ash School), in Chicago, IL in his youth.<ref name="Prodigal Son, Child of The King" /> Raised by his mother Jessie, he was exposed early on to the Christian church and strong religious values,<ref name=" J. O. Patterson Ministry Official Homepage ">{{cite web|title=Home Page |url= http://www.jopattersonministry.com/Home.html|publisher= J. O. Patterson Ministry |accessdate=5 May 2013|pages=1|year=2013}}</ref><ref name="Jadore ">{{cite web|title=Benjamin Jimerson: The Politician of Entertainment |url= http://www.jadoremag.com/take-cover/benjamin-jimerson-the-politician-of-entertainment  |publisher= Jadore |accessdate=5 May 2013|pages=1|year=2009}}</ref> her work as an avid Christian missionary, book author, songwriter and humanitarian inspired him, eventually leading him to contribute and publish a gospel activity book, written and illustrated by his mother "Agape Coloring Activity Book Of Prayers Puzzle Games ".<ref name=" Agape Coloring Activity Book Of Prayers Puzzle Games ">{{cite book|title= Agape Coloring Activity Book Of Prayers Puzzle Games |publisher=Create Space |isbn=1468038230  |accessdate=5 May 2013|type=Hardcover}}</ref><ref name=" Agape Coloring Activity Book Of Prayers Puzzle Games ">{{cite web|title= Agape Coloring Activity Book Of Prayers Puzzle Games |url= https://www.createspace.com/3741396 |publisher= Create Space|accessdate=5 May 2013|pages=1|year=2013}}</ref> 
Jimerson-Philips father  James O. Patterson Sr. being former Presiding Bishop of Church of God In Christ,<ref name="COGIC Discipleship Bible 2007">{{cite book|title=COGIC Discipleship Bible 2007 |publisher=Church of God in Christ  |accessdate=5 May 2013|type=Hardcover}}</ref> also had weight in the Christian church community, being one of the First Elected Presiding Bishop's in the [[Church of God in Christ]] 1968<U+2013>1989.<ref name=COGICInt>[http://cogicinternational.com/history.html "A Brief Historical Sketch of the Church of God in Christ, International (Arkansas)"]. Accessed June 24, 2013.</ref> Jimerson-Philips siblings include sister [[Annette P. Jimerson]] published author and artist,<ref name="WhoWho">{{cite book|title=Who's Who in America 2013.|publisher=Marquis Whos Who|isbn=978-0-8379-7037-0|accessdate=7 October 2012|type=Hardcover}}</ref> and half brother J.O. Patterson Jr. former two term Tennessee Congressman, and Tennessee Senator and first black Mayor for the City of Memphis.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.memphishistory.org/Politics/TheMayorsofMemphis/Biographies4/JOPattersonJr/tabid/265/Default.aspx | title = MemphisHistory.com's page on J.O. Patterson, Jr. | accessdate = 2011-01-01}}</ref><ref>[http://www.commercialappeal.com/news/2011/jul/01/bishop-jo-patterson-jr-honored-hundreds-then-laid/ Bishop J.O. Patterson Jr. blazed trails in religion as well as politics <U+00BB> The Commercial Appeal]</ref> Stephen Wigley Jr.,  and reported half-brothers to Kimmy Brooks Anthony Flagg, and  Kevin Haley all alleged to be children of J.O. Patterson Sr.<ref name="Prodigal Son, Child of The King" /> Other relatives include nieces [[Jessica M. Jimerson]], Tiffany Jimerson, and Angel Jimerson, daughters of his sister [[Annette P. Jimerson]].<ref name=""A Day In The Life"... ">{{cite book|title= "A Day In The Life"... |publisher=Create Space |isbn=1466347724 |accessdate=16 June 2013|type=Hardcover}}</ref>

Also having authored three other published books including Prodigal Son Child of The King,<ref name="Prodigal Son, Child of The King" /> 'Player's School' (Book of Game),<ref name=" 'Player's School' (Book of Game) ">{{cite book|title='Player's School' (Book of Game) |publisher=Create Space |isbn=1453872191  |accessdate=5 May 2013|type=Hardcover}}</ref> and "A Day In The Life... ".<ref name=""A Day In The Life"... ">{{cite book|title= "A Day In The Life"... |publisher=Create Space |isbn=1466347724 |accessdate=16 June 2013|type=Hardcover}}</ref> 
He is also the authored a few convention books for Bishop George D. McKinney of COGIC Southern California Second Jurisdiction, whom he claims as his surrogate Father figure in his Prodigal Son, Child of The King publication.<ref name="Prodigal Son, Child of The King" /> He has also played a supporting role in the career successes of Actor [[David Ramsey]], Jazsmin Lewis, Sam Saletta, and Niki Saletta.<ref name="Jimerson & Associates ">{{cite web|title=Home Page|url= http://www.jimersonandassociates.com/Home.html |publisher= Jimerson & Associates |accessdate=5 May 2013|pages=1|year=2013}}</ref> Before pursuing his dreams in the entertainment field he formed a stage name for himself, reforming his name to Captain Fantastic.<ref name=""A Day In The Life"... ">{{cite book|title= "A Day In The Life"... |publisher=Create Space |isbn=1466347724 |accessdate=16 June 2013|type=Hardcover}}</ref>  Shortly after he began recording and producing a record alongside Charles Allen titled "Undercover Lover" which was an indie release on Right Note Records, release by Captain Fantastic & Star Fleet.<ref name=""A Day In The Life"... ">{{cite book|title= "A Day In The Life"... |publisher=Create Space |isbn=1466347724 |accessdate=16 June 2013|type=Hardcover}}</ref>  The record was about a fictional secret love affair between a man and woman.  Featuring Charles Allen, Lloyd Smith, Mark Bynum (members of the gold record group [[The Bar-Kays]]) as well as band mates Gerald Pride, Nazeeh Islam & Ralph LaVeaux.<ref name=""A Day In The Life"... ">{{cite book|title= "A Day In The Life"... |publisher=Create Space |isbn=1466347724 |accessdate=16 June 2013|type=Hardcover}}</ref> Jimerson-Philips & Allen went on to produce other independent released records including the 1988 release "Playmate" by Kimmi Kim, and 1989 release of "Undercover Lover" on the "I'm Out for Love" album by Revea.<ref name=""A Day In The Life"... ">{{cite book|title= "A Day In The Life"... |publisher=Create Space |isbn=1466347724 |accessdate=16 June 2013|type=Hardcover}}</ref>

Early on in Jimerson-Philips career, he dabbled in the music industry acting as a casting agent, to provide talent for numerous music videos including "[[I Just Wanna Love U (Give It 2 Me)]]", "[[Izzo (H.O.V.A.)|Izzo]]" and "[[Girls, Girls, Girls (Jay-Z song)]] by [[Jay-Z]], In "[[Disco Inferno (50 Cent song)]]", "[[Candy Shop]]" by [[50 Cent]], "[[More Than a Woman (Aaliyah song)|More Than A Woman]]" by [[Aaliyah]], "Thong Song" by Sisqo, Snake", "Fiesta" and "[[If I Could Turn Back the Hands of Time]]" by [[R. Kelly]].<ref name=""A Day In The Life"... ">{{cite book|title= "A Day In The Life"... |publisher=Create Space |isbn=1466347724 |accessdate=16 June 2013|type=Hardcover}}</ref><ref name="Jimerson & Associates" /> As well as other noted project work with Missey Elliott, Gwen Stefani, Black Eyed Peas, and  J-Lo  providing talent in many other videos.<ref name=""A Day In The Life"... ">{{cite book|title= "A Day In The Life"... |publisher=Create Space |isbn=1466347724 |accessdate=16 June 2013|type=Hardcover}}</ref> Interestingly he also appeared briefly in R. Kelly<U+2019>s "If I Could Turn Back The Hand of Time" music video due to a male talent not showing up for the video shoot.<ref name=""A Day In The Life"... ">{{cite book|title= "A Day In The Life"... |publisher=Create Space |isbn=1466347724 |accessdate=16 June 2013|type=Hardcover}}</ref>
Benjamin O. Jimerson-Philips, received multiple Gold & Platinum Record Awards, over the years including [[Brandy]], [[Ginuwine]], [[Paula Abdul]], Expose', [[Vanessa L. Williams|Vanessa Williams]] and [[R. Kelly]].<ref name=""A Day In The Life"... ">{{cite book|title= "A Day In The Life"... |publisher=Create Space |isbn=1466347724 |accessdate=16 June 2013|type=Hardcover}}</ref>
Jimerson-Philips primary focus however is in the film industry,  where his early fascination with film lead him to earn a certificate of completion, at the Hollywood Film Institute for Cinema Director & Line Producer.<ref name="Prodigal Son, Child of The King">{{cite book|title=Prodigal Son, Child of The King |publisher=Create Space |isbn= 1475109881 |accessdate=16 June 2013|type=Hardcover}}</ref> 
He  has  produced five motion pictures<ref name=" Benjamin Jimerson Phillips ">{{cite web|title= Benjamin Jimerson Phillips |url= http://www.istudio.com/25736|publisher=iStudio |accessdate=5 May 2013|pages=1|year=2013}}</ref> including Resurrection: The J.R. Richard Story,<ref name=" Full cast and crew for Resurrection: The J.R. Richard Story">{{cite web|title=Full cast and crew for Resurrection: The J.R. Richard Story |url=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0410516/fullcredits?ref_=tt_cl_sm#cast|publisher=imdb |accessdate=5 May 2013|pages=1|year=2013}}</ref> Waters Rising,<ref name=" Full cast and crew for Waters Rising">{{cite web|title=Full cast and crew for Waters Rising |url=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0762089/fullcredits?ref_=tt_cl_sm#cast|publisher=imdb |accessdate=5 May 2013|pages=1|year=2013}}</ref><ref name="Benjamin Jimerson-Phillips Filmography">{{cite web|title=Full cast and crew for Waters Rising |url= http://www.fandango.com/benjaminjimersonphillips/filmography/p556393|publisher= Fandango|accessdate=5 May 2013|pages=1|year=2013}}</ref><ref name="Benjamin Jimerson-Phillips Filmography">{{cite web|title=Benjamin Jimerson-Phillips Filmography |url= http://www.artistdirect.com/nad/store/movies/principal/filmography/0,,4543851,00.html|publisher= artist Direct |accessdate=5 May 2013|pages=1|year=2013}}</ref>
and Treasure n tha Hood (which he co-produced, starring [[Katt Williams]])<ref name=" Full cast and crew for Treasure n tha Hood">{{cite web|title=Full cast and crew for Treasure n tha Hood |url=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0421262/fullcredits?ref_=tt_cl_sm#cast|publisher=imdb |accessdate=5 May 2013|pages=1|year=2013}}</ref> to name a few.
The biopic movie [[Resurrection: The J.R. Richard Story (film)]], starring [[David Ramsey]],<ref name=" Greg Carter Resurrects a Baseball Hero">{{cite web|title=Greg Carter Resurrects a Baseball Hero |url= http://www.btlnews.com/commentary/director-series/greg-carter-resurrects-a-baseball-hero/ |publisher= BLT News |accessdate=5 May 2013|pages=1|year=2013}}</ref><ref name="Shooting Star">{{cite web|title=Shooting Star |url= http://www.houstonpress.com/2004-09-02/news/shooting-star/
|publisher= Houston Press |accessdate=5 May 2013|pages=1|year=2013}}</ref> Kenya Moore of "Real Housewives of Atlanta", Sara Stokes of "Making The Band", and two time Oscar Nominee Charles Durning all being a well rounded highlight  in Jimerson-Philips film career. In recent years he has been noted for being involved in developing several significant projects for the silver screen,  television and stage<ref name="Jimerson & Associates" /> including the comedy "Player<U+2019>s School",<ref name="Jimerson & Associates" /> as well as reality series "The House of Divas",<ref name="Jimerson & Associates" /> and "Country Girls", WWI film  "Camp Logan". As well as assisting in the development of the stage plays Before We Say I Do and "Celebrate Moma" (with playwright Michael McCurtis).

He has also been Commissioned as a "Goodwill Ambassador" by Arkansas Governors Jim Guy Tucker and Mike Huckabee.<ref name="Prodigal Son, Child of The King" /> In early 2000 he ran for City Council in the city of Little Rock, AR. However Jimerson-Philips ran a self funded campaign and did not accept donations, on the notion that doing so only insured special interest Candidates would win, and not those who have the best values, or visionary plan.<ref name=""A Day In The Life"... ">{{cite book|title= "A Day In The Life"... |publisher=Create Space |isbn=1466347724 |accessdate=16 June 2013|type=Hardcover}}</ref> His television campaign advertisement consisted of commercials by Grammy Award Winning Gospel Recording Artist Andrae Crouch; Actress Jasmine Lewis, and Actor [[David Ramsey]]. 2005 was appointed as a "Colonel" on the Staff of New Mexico Governor Bill Richardson, later he received a Special California State Senate Resolution #728 in 1991 & Resolution #1729 in 2006.<ref name=""A Day In The Life"... ">{{cite book|title= "A Day In The Life"... |publisher=Create Space |isbn=1466347724 |accessdate=16 June 2013|type=Hardcover}}</ref><ref name="Jadore" />

==Education==

*The Hollywood Film Institute, Hollywood, California (2009) Certificate of Completion.<ref name="Prodigal Son, Child of The King" />

*Charles Harrison Mason University, San Diego (1993) Special Certificate from Dr. Myles Munroe &  Bishop George D. McKinney in Biblical Principles of Leadership Development.<ref name="Prodigal Son, Child of The King" />

*Chrispus Attucks School, Chicago, IL.<ref name="Prodigal Son, Child of The King" />

*[[University of Arkansas]], Little Rock, AR.<ref name="Prodigal Son, Child of The King" />

